header.gameNote: COLONIAL ATHLETIC ASSN TR AT RICHMOND VA

article.headline: Towson 67, N.C.-Wilmington 52
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- C.C. Williams and Dennard Abraham combined for nine points in a 15-0 first-half run Friday night, helping Towson to a 67-52 victory against North Carolina-Wilmington in the first round of the Colonial Athletic Association tournament. The Tigers (16-16) advanced to a quarterfinal game against second-seeded Old Dominion on Saturday. N.C.-Wilmington finished 7-22. The Seahakws had a 6-5 lead with 14:02 remaining in the first. Winston Tubbs hit one of two free throws to start the 15-0 run, which left the Tigers with a 20-6 lead with 9:04 remaining. N.C.-Wilmington responded with a 13-3 run paced by nine points from Daniel Fountain. Towson finished with a 29-25 halftime lead. After the Seahawks scored the first basket of the second half, Towson ran off 10-straight points and N.C.-Wilmington could get no closer than six the rest of the way. Gary Neal, the country's fourth-leading scorer, finished with 19 points and a career-high nine rebounds. Abraham added 13 points, Rodney Spruill a career-high 12, and Williams had 11. Fountain led the Seahawks with 16 points and Vladimir Kuljanin added 15.
